results.name: Numbers n such that phi(n)=tau(n)^4, where tau(n)=A000005(n).
comment: For all large enough n, we have tau(n) < n^(1/5) and phi(n) > n^(4/5). Hence, tau(n)^4 < n^(4/5) < phi(n), implying that this sequence is finite. - _Max Alekseyev_, Mar 10 2016
link: Giovanni Resta, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..7000 (first 660 terms from Enrique Pérez Herrero)
